 Boosting INSERT Speed by Generating Scalable Keys 
 
   2011-10-05 
   Grade of the Steel   SQL Server Archive   	
   23 Comments   I/O ,  Keys ,  OLTP ,  Performance ,  Scale ,  SQL Server 
 Throughout history, similar ideas tend to surface at about the same time. Last week, at  SQLBits 9 , I did some “on stage” tuning of the  Paul Randal INSERT challenge . 
 It turns out that at almost the same time, a lab run was being done that demonstrated, on a real world workload, a technique similar to the one I ended up using. You can find it